  "text": "It has been noticed that in young, alert, healthy adults when subjected to an isovolemic hemodilution with a decreased hemoglobin concentration of 12.5 g/dL to 4.8 g/dL that an increased heart rate, systolic volume index and the cardiac index is produced with no systemic evidence of hypoxic changes despite a reduction in the DO 2 (oxygen delivery) to a level of 7.3 mL/kg/ min [CITATION_1] .",
